Be careful when applying growth serum to large animals, especially within hybrids, as it can sometimes decrease the item's overall value.

message: To succeed, focus primarily on the 'Growth Serum'. Combine 2 small animals (e.g., butterfly + bird) with similar features first, then apply the Growth Serum three times to reach the 'ultra-grown' state, yielding values around 30-35. For medium animals (e.g., squid, kangaroo), apply Growth Serum twice to reach 'super-grown' for values around 15. The highest score I achieved was 50 by combining an 'ultra-grown' pair of small animals with a 'super-grown' medium animal. For large animals, apply Growth Serum only once; a second application or mutation will make them negative. Avoid the 'Mutation Catalyst' entirely; every use resulted in negative or zero value, drastically reducing my score from 50 to 5 or 0. Also, do not combine more than three items, as combining four resulted in a -100 penalty.

message: Prioritize the 'growth serum'. For the highest value I found (35), combine two large animals (e.g., elephant+whale) and apply the serum. Another good strategy for a value of 30 is to combine a large and a small animal, apply the serum, then combine that resulting item with a medium animal. Do NOT use the mutation catalyst; it consistently made scores negative in my experience. Be careful not to 'over-grow' items; applying the serum a second time to an already 'grown' 2-component item can result in a 0 value. The maximum of 3 animals per item seems to hold true for positive outcomes.
